document_data.mainbody:
'''Wa-an''', or the '''Wa language''', was a language spoken by the [[Wanese]], inhabitants of [[Wa]] in [[Kara-Tur]].{{Cite dragon/Speaking in Tongues|26}}

Wa-an descended from the ancient [[Han language]], as did [[Koryo language|Koryo]] and [[Kozakuran language|Kozakuran]], and possibly others.

Wa-an was abundant with polite expressions and flowery terminology. Etiquette rather than grammar regulated the proper usage of many phrases.
